`,r.jsxs(n.p,{children:["Difficulties tended to appear as ",r.jsx(n.strong,{children:"application complexity"}),' grew. Imperative DOM updates — select an element, mutate it, bind another handler — can scatter state across the page. In large codebases, answering "what is on screen?" may require tracing selectors instead of reading a single state model. That pain point motivated declarative libraries, including React, Vue, and others — not a failure of jQuery itself, but a different scale of problem.']}),`
